            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;By default perf record uses the frame pointer register. Modern compilers don&apos;t record the frame address and instead use the register as a general purpose. The alternative is to compile with &lt;code&gt;-fno-omit-frame-pointer&lt;/code&gt; flag or use a different alternative: record with &lt;code&gt;--call-graph &quot;dwarf&quot;&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;--call-graph &quot;lbr&quot;&lt;/code&gt; depending on your scenario.&lt;/span&gt;

